	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_42096535">It's not a question of whether it's <i>possible</i> to start from nothing and be well off. It certainly is, for a few select people. The question you should ask yourself is <i>how many</i> succeed (preemptive addendum: even if you only consider those who <i>try</i>). A lot of people fall prey to confirmation bias when they discuss capitalism: they see ten people that succeeded, but not the ten thousand that didn't &mdash; because no one sings the story of those that failed.</div>
	</div>

