	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_42090123">If you believe the <a href="https://en.bitcoin.it/wiki/Mining_hardware_comparison" title="bitcoin.it">mhash/s speeds of (yet to be released) ASIC hardware</a> [bitcoin.it], as well as <a href="https://en.bitcoin.it/wiki/P2Pool" title="bitcoin.it">decentralized P2Pool mining</a> [bitcoin.it], then you'll need to factor in the effect of disruptive technologies on "deflationary spirals". Bitcoin mining was something I was recently evaluating and decided against after <a href="http://bitcoinx.com/profit/index.php" title="bitcoinx.com">researching</a> [bitcoinx.com] and factoring in the effects of profitability decline per year on revenue, especially if ASIC hardware delivers as specced.</div>
