	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_42090939"><p><div class="quote"><p>How on Earth does SETI@Home benefit society? Even if by some bizarre coincidence, we actually detected evidence of intelligent life outside of the solar system, the likelihood that society would benefit by that is basically nil.</p></div><p>Directly, on the positive side, it would pretty much kill some religions, or at least transform them into less harmful variants that don't preach that humans are unique and masters of everything.<br>On the negative side, it would probably trigger some new ones.  If people can believe in Xenu, Kolob, Ezekiel or John's revelation, they most certainly would be able to start cults based on extrasolar intelligence too.  Hopefully, most of them will put on their Nike sneakers and leave us.</p><p>Indirectly, it would likely renew interest in space exploration, which I think might benefit us all, and especially our descendants and their chance of survival.</p></div>
	</div>

